Text: Fake! I checked with "Spectro" (http://spectro.enpts.com/) The music files have been converted from Mp3...
Actually, zelos81, they're not fake. I did a direct rip of the CD, with zero conversion. The CD had AIFF music files.
In addition, Spectro is "currently capable of reading FLAC, APE, MP3 and WAV files"... and these aren't any of those formats.

http://cl.ly/PawV
This makes for 1.35 Mbit/sec bitrate.
It isn't fake. Very nice quality on the rips.
Why use AIFF instead of FLAC?
Well, it's still lossless, so thanks.
